Cladophora.label: Cladophora
Cladophora.description: Cladophora is a genus of reticulated filamentous Ulvophyceae. The genus Cladophora contains many species that are very hard to tell apart and classify, mainly because of the great variation in their ... Wikipedia

Coccomyxa.label: Coccomyxa
Coccomyxa.description: Coccomyxa is a genus of algae, in the family Coccomyxaceae. Wikipedia

Volvocales.label: Volvocales
Volvocales.description: In taxonomy, the Volvocales, also known as Chlamydomonadales, are an order of flagellate or pseudociliate green algae, specifically of the Chlorophyceae. Volvocales can form planar or spherical colonies. These vary from Gonium up to Volvox. Wikipedia

Ostreococcus.label: Ostreococcus
Ostreococcus.description: Ostreococcus is a genus of unicellular coccoid or spherically shaped green alga belonging to the class Prasinophyceae. It includes prominent members of the global picoplankton community, which plays a central role in the oceanic carbon cycle. Wikipedia

Zygnematophyceae.label: Zygnematophyceae
Zygnematophyceae.description: Zygnematophyceae is a class of green algae. It contains two orders Zygnematales and Desmidiales. Wikipedia

Bambusina.label: Bambusina
Bambusina.description: In taxonomy, Bambusina is a genus of fresh-water algae, specifically of the Desmidiaceae. Wikipedia

Chlorella pyrenoidosa.label: Chlorella pyrenoidosa
Chlorella pyrenoidosa.description: Chlorella pyrenoidosa is a species of the freshwater green algae genus Chlorella. It occurs world wide. The species name pyrenoidosa refers to the presence of a prominent pyrenoid within the Chlorella chloroplast. Wikipedia

Closterium.label: Closterium
Closterium.description: In taxonomy, Closterium is a genus of algae, specifically of the family Closteriaceae. Wikipedia

Coleochaete.label: Coleochaete
Coleochaete.description: Coleochaete is a genus of parenchymatous green algae in the family Coleochaetaceae. They are haploid, reproduce asexually, they can be characterised by true multicellular organisation, creating planar ... Wikipedia

Cosmarium.label: Cosmarium
Cosmarium.description: In taxonomy, Cosmarium is a genus of algae, specifically of the Desmidiaceae. Wikipedia

Desmidium.label: Desmidium
Desmidium.description: Desmidium is one of the filamentous desmid genera characterized by rather firm intercellular connections. Cells connect to adjoining cells at the flat, apical face of the cells. The cells can be longer or shorter than wide. Wikipedia

Gonatozygon.label: Gonatozygon
Gonatozygon.description: In taxonomy, Gonatozygon is a genus of algae, specifically of the Gonatozygaceae. Wikipedia

Hyalotheca.label: Hyalotheca
Hyalotheca.description: In taxonomy, Hyalotheca is a genus of algae, specifically of the Desmidiaceae. Wikipedia

Micrasterias.label: Micrasterias
Micrasterias.description:
Micrasterias is a unicellular green alga of the Desmidiales order.
Micrasterias, commonly known as green alga, is a Eukaryotic, unicellular, and ~0.35mm in size. Wikipedia

Oedogonium.label: Oedogonium
Oedogonium.description: Oedogonium is a genus of filamentous green algae, with unbranched filaments that are one cell thick. Oedogonium can be free-floating, though it is usually attached to aquatic plants by a holdfast. It appears greenish and inhabits calm, fresh water. Wikipedia

Pandorina.label: Pandorina
Pandorina.description: Pandorina is a genus of green algae composed of 8, 16, or sometimes 32 cells, held together at their bases to form a sack globular colony surrounded by mucilage. The cells are ovoid or slightly narrowed at one end to appear keystone- or pear-shaped. Wikipedia

Sphaeropleales.label: Sphaeropleales
Sphaeropleales.description: In taxonomy, the Sphaeropleales are an order of green algae that used to be called Chlorococcales. The order includes some of the most common freshwater planktonic algae such as Scenedesmus and Pediastrum. Wikipedia

Staurastrum.label: Staurastrum
Staurastrum.description: In taxonomy, Staurastrum is a genus of algae, specifically of the Desmidiaceae. Wikipedia

Haematococcus.label: Haematococcus
Haematococcus.description: Haematococcus is a genus of algae, specifically of the Haematococcaceae. Members of this group are the common cause for the pink color found in birdbaths. Wikipedia

Actinochloridaceae.label: Actinochloridaceae
Actinochloridaceae.description: Actinochloridaceae is a family of algae, in the order Chlorococcales. Wikipedia

Avrainvillea.label: Avrainvillea
Avrainvillea.description: In taxonomy, Avrainvillea is a genus of algae, specifically of the Udoteaceae. Wikipedia

Chaetosiphon.label: Chaetosiphon
Chaetosiphon.description: In taxonomy, Chaetosiphon is a genus of algae, specifically of the Chaetosiphonaceae. Wikipedia

Chlorococcaceae.label: Chlorococcaceae
Chlorococcaceae.description: Chlorococcaceae is a family of algae, in the order Chlorococcales. Wikipedia

Chlorococcum.label: Chlorococcum
Chlorococcum.description: Chlorococcum is a genus of algae, in the family Chlorococcaceae. Wikipedia

Chlorodesmis.label: Chlorodesmis
Chlorodesmis.description: In taxonomy, Chlorodesmis is a genus of algae, specifically of the Udoteaceae. Algae in this genus produce the toxic diterpene chlorodesmin to defend themselves against generalist herbivores This toxin also kills certain corals that touch the alga. Wikipedia

Closteridium.label: Closteridium
Closteridium.description: Closteridium is a genus of algae, in the family Chlorococcaceae. Wikipedia

Desmococcus.label: Desmococcus
Desmococcus.description: Desmococcus is a genus of algae, in the family Chaetophoraceae. Wikipedia

Dilabifilum.label: Dilabifilum
Dilabifilum.description: Dilabifilum is a genus of thalloid alga comprising approximately 4 species. The thalli take a crustose form. Choreonema reproduces by means of conceptacles; it produces tetraspores and dispores and carpospores. It is a source of agar. Wikipedia

Micractiniaceae.label: Micractiniaceae
Micractiniaceae.description: Micractiniaceae is a family of algae, in the order Chlorococcales. Wikipedia

Nannochloris.label: Nannochloris
Nannochloris.description: Nannochloris is a genus of algae, in the family Coccomyxaceae. Wikipedia

Neochloris oleoabundans.label: Neochloris oleoabundans
Neochloris oleoabundans.description: Neochloris oleoabundans is a microalga belonging in the class Chlorophyceae. Due to its high lipid content, it has been considered as a candidate organism for cosmetics and biofuel production, as well as feed stock for freshwater mussels. Wikipedia

Pringsheimiella.label: Pringsheimiella
Pringsheimiella.description: Pringsheimiella is a genus of algae, in the family Chaetophoraceae. Wikipedia

Pseudobryopsis.label: Pseudobryopsis
Pseudobryopsis.description: In taxonomy, Pseudobryopsis is a genus of algae, specifically of the Bryopsidaceae. Wikipedia

Pseudochaete.label: Pseudochaete
Pseudochaete.description: Pseudochaete is a genus of algae, in the family Chaetophoraceae. However, this genus is not recognized by all authorities, sometimes being considered part of genus Stigeoclonium. Wikipedia

Spondylosium.label: Spondylosium
Spondylosium.description: In taxonomy, Spondylosium is a genus of algae, specifically of the Desmidiaceae. Wikipedia

Sphaerozosma.label: Sphaerozosma
Sphaerozosma.description: In taxonomy, Sphaerozosma is a genus of algae, specifically of the Desmidiaceae. Wikipedia

Staurodesmus.label: Staurodesmus
Staurodesmus.description: In taxonomy, Staurodesmus is a genus of algae, specifically of the Desmidiaceae. Wikipedia

Tetraselmis.label: Tetraselmis
Tetraselmis.description: Tetraselmis is a genus of phytoplankton. Tetraselmis has a very high lipid level; their amino acids stimulate feeding in marine organisms. Tetraselmis is green, motile, and usually grows 10 µm long x 14 µm wide. Wikipedia

Trichosolen.label: Trichosolen
Trichosolen.description: In taxonomy, Trichosolen is a genus of algae, specifically of the Bryopsidaceae. Wikipedia

Bryopsidales.label: Bryopsidales
Bryopsidales.description: Bryopsidales is an order of green algae, in the class Bryopsidophyceae. Wikipedia

Halimeda tuna.label: Halimeda tuna
Halimeda tuna.description:
Halimeda tuna is a species of green macroalgae.
Halimeda tuna is the type species of the genus Halimeda. Wikipedia

Nitella.label: Nitella
Nitella.description: Nitella is a genus of alga in the family Characeae. Wikipedia

Nitella flexilis.label: Nitella flexilis
Nitella flexilis.description: Nitella flexilis is a freshwater species of characean algae that is used as a model organism for its large cell size and relative ease of cultivation in the laboratory. Wikipedia

Chaetophorales.label: Chaetophorales
Chaetophorales.description: In taxonomy, the Chaetophorales are an order of green algae, specifically the Chlorophyceae. Wikipedia

Chlorococcales.label: Chlorococcales
Chlorococcales.description: Chlorococcales is an order of green algae in the class Chlorophyceae. Individual specimens are sometimes found in soil, but mostly in fresh and marine waters. The order contains approximately 780 species. Wikipedia

Ctenocladales.label: Ctenocladales
Ctenocladales.description: In taxonomy, the Ctenocladales are an order of green algae, specifically the Trebouxiophyceae. Wikipedia

Chlamydomonas.label: Chlamydomonas
Chlamydomonas.description: Chlamydomonas is a genus of green algae consisting of unicellular flagellates, found in stagnant water and on damp soil, in freshwater, seawater, and even in snow as "snow algae". Wikipedia

Pediastrum.label: Pediastrum
Pediastrum.description: Pediastrum is a genus of algae, in the family Hydrodictyaceae. It is a nonmotile coenobial green algae that inhabits freshwater environments. Wikipedia

Ulvophyceae.label: Ulvophyceae
Ulvophyceae.description: The Ulvophyceae or ulvophytes are a class of green algae, distinguished mainly on the basis of ultrastructural morphology, life cycle and molecular phylogenetic data. The sea lettuce, Ulva, belongs here. Wikipedia

Chara vulgaris.label: Chara vulgaris
Chara vulgaris.description: Chara vulgaris is a green alga species in the genus Chara. Wikipedia

Charales.label: Charales
Charales.description: Charales is an order of pondweeds, algae in the division Charophyta. They are green plants believed to be the closest relatives of the green land plants. Linnaeus established the genus Chara in 1753. Wikipedia

Euastrum.label: Euastrum
Euastrum.description: In taxonomy, Euastrum is a genus of algae, specifically of the Desmidiaceae. Wikipedia

Uronema.label: Uronema
Uronema.description: Uronema is a genus of algae, in the family Chaetophoraceae. Wikipedia

Zygnema.label: Zygnema
Zygnema.description: Zygnema is a genus of freshwater filamentous thalloid alga comprising about 100 species. A terrestrial species, Z. terrestre, is known from India. Wikipedia

Pediastrum duplex.label: Pediastrum duplex
Pediastrum duplex.description:
Pediastrum duplex is a type species of green, fresh water algae in the genus pediastrum.
They form nonmotile coenobia with a fixed number of cells. These coenobia are flat and have a circular shape. Wikipedia

Brachiomonas.label: Brachiomonas
Brachiomonas.description: Brachiomonas is a genus of thalloid biflagellate green alga. These algae generally are found in marine or brackish waters, but can tolerate wide range of salinities. Wikipedia

Bryopsidella.label: Bryopsidella
Bryopsidella.description: In taxonomy, Bryopsidella is a genus of algae, specifically of the Bryopsidaceae. Wikipedia

Characiosiphon.label: Characiosiphon
Characiosiphon.description: Characiosiphon is a genus of algae, in the family Characiosiphonaceae. Wikipedia

Chlorochytrium.label: Chlorochytrium
Chlorochytrium.description: Chlorochytrium is a genus of algae, in the family Endosphaeraceae. Wikipedia

Chlorohippotes.label: Chlorohippotes
Chlorohippotes.description: Chlorohippotes is a genus of algae, in the family Chlorococcaceae. Wikipedia

Codiolum.label: Codiolum
Codiolum.description: Codiolum is a genus of algae, in the family Endosphaeraceae. Wikipedia

Coelastraceae.label: Coelastraceae
Coelastraceae.description: A family of green algae in the order Chlorococcales. Colonial algae usually arranged 3 dimensionally in spherical to loosely spherical shapes. Individual cells connected to each other via cell wall extensions. Wikipedia

Deasonia.label: Deasonia
Deasonia.description: Deasonia is a genus of algae, in the family Actinochloridaceae. Wikipedia

Derbesia.label: Derbesia
Derbesia.description: Derbesia is a genus of green algae, specifically of the Derbesiaceae. The plant was originally known from different names applied to its larger sporophyte, Derbesia, and its less conspicuous gametophyte, Halicystis. Wikipedia

Dermatophyton.label: Dermatophyton
Dermatophyton.description: In taxonomy, Dermatophyton is a genus of algae, in the family Chaetophoraceae. Wikipedia

Dictyosphaerium.label: Dictyosphaerium
Dictyosphaerium.description: Dictyosphaerium is a genus of algae, in the family Dictyosphaeriaceae. Wikipedia

Chlorella.label: Chlorella
Chlorella.description: Chlorella is a genus of single-cell green algae, belonging to the phylum Chlorophyta. It is spherical in shape, about 2 to 10 μm in diameter, and is without flagella. Wikipedia

Fritschiella.label: Fritschiella
Fritschiella.description: Fritschiella is a genus of algae, in the family Chaetophoraceae. Wikipedia
